## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-103">El <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control proporciona las siguientes capacidades:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-103">The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control provides the following capabilities:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-104">**Navegación**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Source%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.NavigateToStream%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.NavigateToString%2A>y <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Refresh%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-104">**Navigation**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Source%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.NavigateToStream%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.NavigateToString%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Refresh%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-105">**Duración de la navegación**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigating>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigated>, y <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.LoadCompleted>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-105">**Navigation Lifetime**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigating>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Navigated>, and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.LoadCompleted>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-106">**Diario de navegación**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoBack%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoBack%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoForward%2A>, y <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoForward%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-106">**Navigation Journaling**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoBack%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoBack%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoForward%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoForward%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-107">**Interoperabilidad WPF/HTML**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.InvokeScript%2A> y <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.ObjectForScripting%2A>, y <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Document%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-107">**WPF/HTML Interoperability**: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.InvokeScript%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.ObjectForScripting%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.Document%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-108"><xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> está limitado por las restricciones de seguridad de la [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] aplicación que hospeda el <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser>:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-108"><xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> is bound by the security constraints of the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] application that is hosting the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser>:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="d7575-109">Cuando <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> está hospedada en plena confianza [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] aplicación (una aplicación independiente, por ejemplo), <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> puede hospedar [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_html](~/includes/tla2sharptla-html-md.md)] documentos desde cualquier ubicación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-109">When <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> is hosted by a full-trust [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] application (a stand-alone application, for example), <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> can host [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_html](~/includes/tla2sharptla-html-md.md)] documents from any location.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="d7575-110">Cuando <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> está hospedada en una confianza parcial [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] aplicación (un [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xbap-md.md)], por ejemplo), <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> solo puede hospedar documentos constituidos **sitio de origen** archivos de datos de aplicación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-110">When <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> is hosted by a partial-trust [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/includes/tla2sharptla-wpf-md.md)] application (an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xbap-md.md)], for example), <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> can only host documents that are **Site Of Origin** application data files.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-111">Para obtener más información, vea [Archivos de recursos, contenido y datos de aplicaciones de WPF](~/docs/framework/wpf/app-development/wpf-application-resource-content-and-data-files.md).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-111">For more information, see [WPF Application Resource, Content, and Data Files](~/docs/framework/wpf/app-development/wpf-application-resource-content-and-data-files.md).</span></span>  
  
> [!CAUTION]
>  <span data-ttu-id="d7575-112">El <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control internamente crea una instancia del control WebBrowser ActiveX nativo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-112">The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control internally instantiates the native WebBrowser ActiveX control.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-113">WPF habilita las características de seguridad aplicando controles de características para el control WebBrowser ActiveX.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-113">WPF enables security features by applying feature controls to the WebBrowser ActiveX control.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-114">Se diferencian los controles de característica que se aplican para XBAP y aplicaciones independientes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-114">The feature controls that are applied differ for XBAPs and stand-alone applications.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-115">Algunas aplicaciones deberían aplicar controles de características adicionales para impedir que se ejecute contenido malintencionado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-115">Some applications should apply additional feature controls to prevent malicious content from running.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-116">Para obtener más información, vea la sección "Controles de característica y Control WebBrowser" en [seguridad (WPF)](~/docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md) y [descripción general de Control WebBrowser y tutoriales](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=179388).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-116">For more information, see the "WebBrowser Control and Feature Controls" section in [Security (WPF)](~/docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md) and [WebBrowser Control Overviews and Tutorials](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=179388).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-117">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo configurar <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> para navegar hasta una [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_html](~/includes/tla2sharptla-html-md.md)] documento usando únicamente el marcado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-117">The following example shows how to configure <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> to navigate to an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_html](~/includes/tla2sharptla-html-md.md)] document by using markup only.</span></span>  
  
```xaml  
<!-- Web Browser Control that hosts a web page. -->  
<WebBrowser x:Name="webBrowser" Source="http://msdn.com"   
  Width="600" Height="600"  />  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-118">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo configurar <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> para navegar a un documento mediante el uso de marcado y código subyacente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-118">The following example shows how to configure <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> to navigate to a document by using markup and code-behind.</span></span>  
  
```xaml  
<StackPanel>  
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">  
        <TextBox x:Name="addressTextBox" Width="200" />  
        <Button Click="goNavigateButton_Click">Go</Button>  
    </StackPanel>  
    <WebBrowser x:Name="myWebBrowser" />  
</StackPanel>  
```  
  
```csharp  
private void goNavigateButton_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)  
{  
    // Get URI to navigate to  
    Uri uri = new Uri(this.addressTextBox.Text, UriKind.RelativeOrAbsolute);  
  
    // Only absolute URIs can be navigated to  
    if (!uri.IsAbsoluteUri)  
    {  
        MessageBox.Show("The Address URI must be absolute eg 'http://www.microsoft.com'");  
        return;  
    }  
  
    // Navigate to the desired URL by calling the .Navigate method  
    this.myWebBrowser.Navigate(uri);  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-119">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo controlar la `NewWindow2` eventos y eventos similares mediante un <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-119">The following example shows how to handle the `NewWindow2` event and similar events using a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-120">Este ejemplo requiere una referencia a **SHDocVw.dll**, `using System.Runtime.InteropServices;` (instrucción) y un <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control denominado `webBrowser1`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-120">This example requires a reference to **SHDocVw.dll**, a `using System.Runtime.InteropServices;` statement, and a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control named `webBrowser1`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public MainWindow()  
{  
    InitializeComponent();  
  
    var serviceProvider = (IServiceProvider)webBrowser1.Document;  
    if (serviceProvider != null)  
    {  
        Guid serviceGuid = new Guid("0002DF05-0000-0000-C000-000000000046");  
        Guid iid = typeof(SHDocVw.WebBrowser).GUID;  
        var webBrowserPtr = (SHDocVw.WebBrowser)serviceProvider  
            .QueryService(ref serviceGuid, ref iid);  
        if (webBrowserPtr != null)  
        {  
            webBrowserPtr.NewWindow2 += webBrowser1_NewWindow2;  
        }  
    }  
}  
  
private void webBrowser1_NewWindow2(ref object ppDisp, ref bool Cancel)  
{  
    // Handle the event.  
}  
  
[ComImport, InterfaceType(ComInterfaceType.InterfaceIsIUnknown)]  
[Guid("6d5140c1-7436-11ce-8034-00aa006009fa")]  
internal interface IServiceProvider  
{  
    [return: MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.IUnknown)]  
    object QueryService(ref Guid guidService, ref Guid riid);  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="d7575-126">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo navegar hasta el documento anterior mediante una llamada a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoBack%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-126">The following example shows how to navigate back to the previous document by calling <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.GoBack%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d7575-127">En el ejemplo se comprueba primero si hay documentos para volver a comprobando <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoBack%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d7575-127">The example first checks that there are documents to navigate back to by checking <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser.CanGoBack%2A>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
private void backButton_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)  
{  
  // Navigate to the previous HTML document, if there is one  
  if (this.webBrowser.CanGoBack)  
  {  
    this.webBrowser.GoBack();  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
